@startuml boundary_failsafe_to_gateway_security_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Boundary Fail-safe To Gateway Security Signal Flow\n(boundary/fail-safe/service context -> SGW diagnostic security seams)

participant "Core / boundary /\nservice context" as BoundaryCtx #F4F7FB
participant "SGW\ngateway security owner" as SGW #E8F7E8
participant "Diag seams /\ngateway state" as DiagBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / testers" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Boundary / Service Inputs ==

BoundaryCtx -> SGW : domainBoundaryStatus\nwarningPathStatus\nfailSafeMode\nrouteActive\nalertLevel
SGW -> SGW : diagStage = ethDiagBoundaryStage(...)
SGW -> SGW : securitySession derived from diagStage / routeActive / authState
SGW -> SGW : securityFault = ethDiagStageToSecurityFault(diagStage)
SGW -> SGW : securityPolicy = ethDiagStageToPolicy(diagStage)
note right of SGW
Representative gating inputs
- boundaryAlive
- warningPathStatus
- failSafeMode
- routeActive / alertLevel
end note

== Security Publish ==

SGW -> DiagBus : Diag::SecurityState / RouteOwner
SGW -> DiagBus : Diag::SessionState / GatewayOpen
SGW -> DiagBus : Diag::SecurityFault / SecurityPolicy
note right of SGW
Representative outputs
- SecurityState
- RouteOwner
- SessionState
- SecurityFault / SecurityPolicy
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

DiagBus -> Obs : gateway security readback /\ndiagnostic test evidence

note over BoundaryCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Boundary and fail-safe context reach SGW
2. SGW derives diagnostic stage and security session
3. SGW publishes security state and route owner seams
4. Testers and observers see the current gateway security posture
end note

@enduml
